## Interactive Components
Since we are using MDX feel free to create react components as interactive examples if applicable.

End each lesson with an interactive exercise using this component:

<InteractiveExercises href="<link to lesson>">
<!-- Brief, clear description of the exercise, Example below -->
Ready to try it yourself? Head over to the Image Optimization Exercise where you'll:

- Implement responsive images
- Configure remote image domains
- Add blur-up placeholders
- Optimize above-the-fold images

</InteractiveExercises>


## Adding to Constants
New lessons must be added to one of the category lists in the constants.ts file with this format:

 {
    id: 'server-components',
    title: 'Server Components',
    description: 'Learn how to use server components in Next.js',
    category: categories['Client & Server'],
    difficulty: difficulties['intermediate'],
    order: 1,
    featured: true,
    status: statuses.completed,
    isDisplayed: isDisplayed.true,
  }

The lesson folder name must match the `id` exactly. For example, a lesson with id 'server-components' must use that exact name for its folder.